olive oil
1 packet Chorizo & Salchichon Pizza
1 tomato
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing

• Preheat oven to 220°C/ 200°C fan-forced.
• Bake chorizo & salchichon pizza directly on wire oven rack in the oven until cheese is
melted and golden, 12-15 minutes.

TIP: Placing the pizza directly onto the wire racks helps the base to crisp up.

• Meanwhile, roughly chop tomato.
• When the pizza has 5 minutes remaining, combine salad leaves, tomato and
balsamic & olive oil dressing in a medium bowl.

• Slice chorizo and salchichon pizza.
• Divide pizza between plates. Serve with balsamic garden salad. Enjoy!